{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"diskInject","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The script runs automatically when macOS starts — no SSH,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"no agent, no network, and no manual setup required. This is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the only provisioning mode that works on a completely vanilla","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS installation from an IPSW.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"How it works:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Before the VM boots, Spooktacular mounts"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the guest’s data volume on the host and writes a standard"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS LaunchDaemon that executes your script at boot time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Best for:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Fresh VMs created from IPSW where you need","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"zero-touch automation — CI runners, test environments,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automated fleet provisioning.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Requires:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Nothing in the guest. Works with any macOS.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/provisioningmode\/diskinject"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode\/diskInject","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text"